grid
css grid
use firefox to test, it can show the grids:
<head>
<style>
.wrapper{
	display:grid;
	grid-template-columns: 70% 30%;
	/*grid-column-gap:1em;
	grid-row-gap:1em;
	can use fractions grid-template-colums: 1fr 2fr 1fr
	use colums:repeat( 3, 1fr), this give 3 1fr columns*/

	grid-gap:1em;
	grid-auto-rows: minmax(100px, auto);
	justify-items:stretch; /* default. begin, end,centre*/
	align-items:top/* centre, bottom*/
}
.wrapper > div{
	background:#eee;
	padding:1em;
}
.wrapper > div:nth-child(odd){
	background:#ddd;
}
</style>
</head>
